snippet.textDisplay: I used to watch Jon on The Daily Show religiously. I still miss him, especially in these times. Now, I find myself so overwhelmed & exhausted by politics, I stopped watching the news several months ago. Now, I  just try to glance at my news feeds (so I know we didn’t bomb some country the night before), bc it’s seems mostly like political kabuki theatre 24/7. However, I’d give almost anything to watch Jon Stewart again on a show of his own as I miss his voice & humor amidst the madness, & I will absolutely watch his movie.

snippet.textDisplay: For many years Jon Stewart was the voice of reason for accountability in politics. Best use of satire comedy ever. He left at a time when he could’ve kept shining with Trump as president. Now he’s like that uncle who just got out of rehab and everyone pretends they are listening to; when all we are really thinking is.. should we buy him a razor and a shirt without mustard stains on it?? He just came out from under the desk, again. It’s sad and humiliating. Miss you Jon. Good luck with the movie.
